    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMarkdown files in Neovim are not rendered in a visually rich way like in VS Code. Headings, tables, checkboxes, code blocks, images, and links are mostly shown as plain text, which makes documentation harder to read and navigate.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd markdown rendering support similar to VS Code’s markdown preview experience. Markdown elements should be visually formatted inside Neovim for better readability and documentation workflow, ideally with proper styling for headings, tables, lists, code blocks, and embedded content.",
